## 6. Indicator Computation

### 🟡 6.1 — [calculateBOLL](file:///home/Sherk/code/ViewingChart/frontend/src/utils/indicators.ts#37-67) has O(n × period) double-pass *(Medium)*

**Files:** [indicators.ts](file:///home/Sherk/code/ViewingChart/frontend/src/utils/indicators.ts#L38-L66)

The Bollinger Bands function iterates the window twice (once for mean, once for variance), giving O(n × 2p) complexity. For 1,000 data points with period=20, that's 40,000 iterations.

**Fix:** Use a rolling sum / rolling sum-of-squares approach for O(n) computation.

### 🟡 6.2 — [calculateSMA](file:///home/Sherk/code/ViewingChart/frontend/src/utils/indicators.ts#3-19) has O(n × period) inner loop *(Medium)*

**Files:** [indicators.ts](file:///home/Sherk/code/ViewingChart/frontend/src/utils/indicators.ts#L4-L18)

```typescript
for (let j = 0; j < period; j++) {
    sum += data[i - j].close;  // recomputed from scratch every iteration
}
```

**Fix:** Use a sliding window that adds the new value and subtracts the old:
```typescript
let sum = 0;
for (let i = 0; i < data.length; i++) {
    sum += data[i].close;
    if (i >= period) sum -= data[i - period].close;
    if (i >= period - 1) result.push({ time: data[i].time, value: sum / period });
}
```

